25|$|The {{franking}} privilege allows <b>members</b> <b>of</b> <b>Congress</b> <b>to</b> send official mail to constituents at government expense. Though {{they are}} not permitted to send election materials, borderline material is often sent, especially in the run-up to an election by those in close races. Indeed, some academics consider free mailings as giving incumbents a big advantage over challengers.|$|E
