50|$|Jeanette Ranking was a 1902 {{graduate}} of UM. She {{was a social}} worker and suffragist. Jeannette {{was the first woman}} elected <b>to</b> U.S. <b>Congress</b> in 1916 and was re-elected in 1940. She was the only <b>member</b> <b>of</b> <b>Congress</b> <b>to</b> vote against the United States' entry into both world wars.|$|R
